    "image_with_text_4hbz8q": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_zXiAWy": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "✨ Bring one less plastic item into your home",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "text_YXUAL3": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The toxic “forever chemicals” known as PFAs found in pet food packaging affect your dog’s health even more than yours: Average blood levels of chemicals from plastics are much higher in pets than in humans. (source: <a href=\"https://ewg.org\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://ewg.org\">ewg.org</a>)</p><h2>✨ Plastic recycling is a myth </h2><p>You may be putting plastic in your recycling bin, but only 5-6% of plastic is being recycled and made into new items. Meanwhile humans currently produce more than 350 million metric tons of plastic waste per year.</p><h2>✨ Most “eco” packaging either contains plastic, or is plastic</h2><p>Not our packages! We've worked hard to source bags, tubes, and labels that are free of plastic coatings and adhesives and can be composted at home. </p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
